:["Some characteristic forenames:  Spanish Francisco, Jose, Manuel, Jesus, Carlos, Juan, Luis, Mario, Miguel, Pablo, Ramon, Ricardo.  Portuguese Joao.  Italian Salvatore, Antonio, Maurizio, Ottavio.","Spanish: variant or altered form of <b>Martínez</b> (see   Martinez  ). This surname is most common in Mexico and Brazil. It has also been established in southern Italy, mainly in Sicily, since the period of Spanish dominance there."],"variants":[{"name":"Martinez","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Spanish Manuel, Carlos, Luis, Jesus, Francisco, Pedro, Miguel, Raul, Mario, Jorge, Roberto, Ruben.  Portuguese Ligia, Paulo, Armanda, Catarina, Gonsalo, Marcio, Wenceslao, Anatolio, Godofredo, Lidio, Sil, Zulmira.","Spanish (<b>Martínez</b>): patronymic from the personal name   Martin  . This surname has also been established in southern Italy since the period of Spanish dominance there. In the US, it is the tenth most frequent surname. Compare   De Martinez  ."]}]},{"name":"Felipa","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From Greek.  See  <b>Philip</b> ."],"variants":[{"name":"Philip","meanings":["From the Greek name <i>Philippos</i>, meaning ‘lover of horses’, from <i>philein</i> ‘to love’ + <i>hippos</i> ‘horse’. This was popular in the classical period and since. It was the name of the father of  Alexander the Great . It was also the name of one of Christ's apostles, of a deacon ordained by the apostles after the death of Christ, and of several other early saints.  See also  Philippa ."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1354684,"age":40,"year":"1200","julianDay":2159351,"description":"The Christian territory controlled the Kingdoms of Aragon, Navarre, and Castile.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"Yrsina Felipa Martines was born in 1160, in Toledo, Castilla-La Mancha, Spain. She had at least 1 daughter with José Bernardo Domingues."},"et":{"1160–":"1160–Surnud","1156–Male":"1156